44:29.494 --> 44:31.289
who died this evening.

44:32.428 --> 44:35.258
Sasha asked me to
read something to you.

44:36.674 --> 44:40.298
I have the privilege
of doing this now.

44:41.679 --> 44:45.337
I would like to thank my
doctors and hospital staff,

44:45.337 --> 44:47.408
who did all they could for me.

44:48.547 --> 44:50.791
I would like to thank
the British police

44:50.791 --> 44:54.243
for pursuing my case with
vigor and professionalism.

44:55.623 --> 44:59.627
I would like to thank my
wife, Marina, who stood by me.

45:00.732 --> 45:04.702
My love for her and our
son knows no bounds.

45:05.564 --> 45:06.945
But as I lie here,

45:08.153 --> 45:12.088
I can distinctly hear
the beating of wings

45:12.088 --> 45:13.607
of the angel of death.

45:14.712 --> 45:18.129
I think therefore, that
this may be the time

45:18.129 --> 45:22.443
to say one or two things
to the person responsible.

45:24.549 --> 45:27.897
You may succeed in silencing me,

45:27.897 --> 45:31.280
but the howl of protest
from around the world

45:31.280 --> 45:35.353
will reverberate, Mr.
Putin, in your ears

45:35.353 --> 45:37.769
for the rest of your life.

45:40.185 --> 45:43.671
May God forgive you
for what you have done,

45:43.671 --> 45:48.676
not only to me, but to our
beloved Russia and its people.

